data.value: Qaitbay Citadel, built between 1477 and 1479 CE by Sultan Al-Ashraf Sayf al-Din Qaitbay, stands on the ruins of the ancient Lighthouse of Alexandria on Pharos Island. Its strategic position was meant to protect Alexandria from naval invasions. The citadel consists of a large square fortress, surrounded by thick walls and towers, with an internal mosque and defensive structures across three levels.
